2: "Richard, in being so fierce toward my vampire, you were doing
3: what you wanted to do, even though you thought it was going to hurt
4: somebody else. He even told you he'd be hurt if..."
5: "He was going to suck my blood!"
6: "Which is what we do to anyone when we tell them we'll be hurt
7: if they don't live our way."
9: "The thing that puzzles you," he said, "is an accepted saying that
10: happens to be impossible.  The phrase is hurt somebody else.  We choose,
11: ourselves, to be hurt or not to be hurt, no matter what.  Us who decides.
12: Nobody else.  My vampire told you he'd be hurt if you didn't let him?  That's
13: his decision to be hurt, that's his choice.  What you do about it is your
14: decision, your choice: give him blood; ignore him; tie him up; drive a stake
15: through his heart.  If he doesn't want the holly stake, he's free to resist,
16: in whatever way he wants.  It goes on and on, choices, choices."
17: "When you look at it that way..."
18: "Listen," he said, "it's important.  We are all.  Free.  To do.
